Here's a simplified JSON representation of a data mesh architecture for a large enterprise:

```json
{
    "type": "software_architecture",
    "title": "Data Mesh Architecture",
    "nodes": [
        {
            "id": "data-domain-1",
            "label": "Data Domain 1",
            "type": "domain",
            "description": "Data and services related to Domain 1",
            "technology": "Data Mesh"
        },
        {
            "id": "data-domain-2",
            "label": "Data Domain 2",
            "type": "domain",
            "description": "Data and services related to Domain 2",
            "technology": "Data Mesh"
        },
        {
            "id": "data-platform",
            "label": "Data Platform",
            "type": "platform",
            "description": "Centralized data platform providing self-serve infrastructure",
            "technology": "Data Mesh"
        },
        {
            "id": "data-product-1",
            "label": "Data Product 1",
            "type": "data-product",
            "description": "Data product for Domain 1",
            "technology": "Data Mesh"
        },
        {
            "id": "data-product-2",
            "label": "Data Product 2",
            "type": "data-product",
            "description": "Data product for Domain 2",
            "technology": "Data Mesh"
        },
        {
            "id": "compute-governance",
            "label": "Compute Governance",
            "type": "governance",
            "description": "Federated computational governance",
            "technology": "Data Mesh"
        }
    ],
    "connections": [
        {
            "from": "data-domain-1",
            "to": "data-product-1",
            "label": "Data ownership",
            "type": "ownership",
            "protocol": "Data Mesh"
        },
        {
            "from": "data-domain-2",
            "to": "data-product-2",
            "label": "Data ownership",
            "type": "ownership",
            "protocol": "Data Mesh"
        },
        {
            "from": "data-product-1",
            "to": "data-platform",
            "label": "Data storage",
            "type": "storage",
            "protocol": "Data Mesh"
        },
        {
            "from": "data-product-2",
            "to": "data-platform",
            "label": "Data storage",
            "type": "storage",
            "protocol": "Data Mesh"
        },
        {
            "from": "data-platform",
            "to": "compute-governance",
            "label": "Compute requests",
            "type": "request",
            "protocol": "Data Mesh"
        }
    ],
    "clusters": [
        {
            "id": "data-layer",
            "label": "Data Layer",
            "nodes": ["data-domain-1", "data-domain-2", "data-product-1", "data-product-2", "data-platform"]
        },
        {
            "id": "governance-layer",
            "label": "Governance Layer",
            "nodes": ["compute-governance"]
        }
    ],
    "styles": {
        "data-domain-1": {"color": "#f4cccc", "shape": "diamond", "border": "dotted"},
        "data-domain-2": {"color": "#f4cccc", "shape": "diamond", "border": "dotted"},
        "data-platform": {"color": "#d3d3d3", "shape": "box", "border": "solid"},
        "data-product-1": {"color": "#c0c0c0", "shape": "ellipse", "border": "dashed"},
        "data-product-2": {"color": "#c0c0c0", "shape": "ellipse", "border": "dashed"},
        "compute-governance": {"color": "#95a5a6", "shape": "parallelogram", "border": "double"}
    }
}
```

This JSON represents a data mesh architecture with two data domains, a centralized data platform, two data products, and a federated compute governance layer. Each data domain owns its data and provides data products for consumption. Data products are stored in the centralized data platform, and compute requests are managed by the compute governance layer.

Note that this JSON representation is a simplified version of a real data mesh architecture and may require modifications to suit your specific needs.
